entry.title: Reading notes for Real and Complex Analysis
entry.content: It’s just a note for books and other materials i’ve read during winter/sommer break in 2019 and for courses “Algebra and Complex Analysis”/“Analysis 3”/“Algebra II” at HU Berlin. And it’s more likely to be my self-training for scientific writing,so it would have lots of mistaskes or looks like “not even wrong”. ~Keep Updating~ 03/06 Artikel created,topics Bieberbach Conjecture and Riemann mapping theorem were added07/28 The Topic “Measure and Integration” Updated08/12 The Topic “ODE and Dynamical Systems” Upadated08/12 The Topic “Integral on Mannifolds” Bieberbach’s Conjecture In the following,D means unit disk and S means the set of all schlicht(i.e. one-to-one holomorphic) functions. “Vielleicht ist überhaupt $k_n = n$.”(L.Bieberbach,1916) Mittag-Leffler Theorem,Weierstrass Factorization Theorem and Coherent Analytic SheafFrom Riemann Mapping Theorem to Uniformization TheoremPicard’s Theorem and Neavanlinna Theory
